doc:
Game module for Love Letter 2019 Premium Edition (ZK Version)
 Contains core game logic with Zero-Knowledge Proof support
 Cards are hidden using commitments, verified with ZK proofs

start_round.doc:
Start a new round - dealer commits to shuffled deck and deals cards
 Called by the dealer (room creator or designated player)
 
 Parameters:
 - deck_commitment: Merkle root of shuffled deck
 - player_commitments: Each player's initial card commitment
 - public_cards: For 2-player games, 3 revealed cards

update_commitment.doc: Update player's card commitment (after drawing a card)

play_turn.doc:
Play a card - reveals the card being played, updates commitment for remaining card
 Some cards require target to respond with ZK proof

execute_guard.doc: Guard - initiates pending action for target to prove

respond_guard.doc: Respond to Guard with ZK proof

execute_priest.doc: Priest - just emits event, target reveals privately to player

execute_baron.doc: Baron - initiates comparison, requires proof from one party

respond_baron.doc: Respond to Baron with ZK proof of comparison result

execute_prince.doc: Prince - target must discard and draw

respond_prince.doc: Respond to Prince - reveal discarded card and new commitment

respond_king.doc: Respond to King - both players submit new commitments

resolve_chancellor.doc: Resolve Chancellor - player submits new commitment after choosing card

handle_timeout.doc: Handle timeout when player doesn't respond to pending action

Player.doc: Player state - NO plaintext cards stored, only commitments

card_commitment.doc:
Commitment to current card(s): hash(card || salt)
 For single card: 32 bytes
 For two cards: 64 bytes (two commitments concatenated)

hand_count.doc: Number of cards in hand (1 or 2)

discarded.doc: Discarded cards (public info - revealed when played)

PendingAction.doc: Pending action that requires ZK proof response

ZKGameRoom.doc: Game room with ZK support - shared object

deck_commitment.doc: Merkle root commitment of shuffled deck

deck_size.doc: Number of cards remaining in deck

RoomRegistry.doc: Registry to track all active rooms

ZKVerificationKeys.doc: ZK Verification Keys - stored once, used for all games

card_ownership_vk.doc: Verification key for card ownership proofs

guard_pvk.doc: Prepared verification key for Guard (Sui format)

baron_pvk.doc: Prepared verification key for Baron (Sui format)
